description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshcore/adapter.c
Lines: 535-550 (valid_default_flood_name)

```c
static bool valid_default_flood_name(const uint8_t *payload)
{
    const uint8_t *nul = memchr(payload, 0,
                    LICHEN_MESHCORE_DEFAULT_FLOOD_NAME_LEN);
    size_t len;

    if (nul == NULL || nul == payload) {
        return false;
    }

    len = (size_t)(nul - payload);
    if (len > 30U) {  // Magic number - why 30 and not 31?
        return false;
    }
    return valid_utf8_text(payload, len);
}
```

Issues:
1. Magic number 30 is used instead of a named constant. LICHEN_MESHCORE_DEFAULT_FLOOD_NAME_LEN is 31, but the check is len > 30. This allows names up to 30 characters, leaving 1 byte for null terminator. Should be documented.

2. The memchr searches for null in 31 bytes, finds it, then checks len > 30. If the null is at exactly position 30 (31st byte), nul - payload = 30, and 30 > 30 is false, so it passes. But the name is 30 chars + null = 31 bytes total, which fills the buffer exactly. This is probably correct but confusing.

Consider using LICHEN_MESHCORE_DEFAULT_FLOOD_NAME_LEN - 1 instead of magic 30.
